♪♪

1259
00:56:14,159 --> 00:56:17,260
♪♪

1260
00:56:17,352 --> 00:56:19,612
Watch this, sunshine.

1261
00:56:19,636 --> 00:56:23,010
♪♪

1262
00:56:23,221 --> 00:56:24,862
That is the fastest thing
I've...

1263
00:56:24,948 --> 00:56:27,667
Why is it faster than me?

1264
00:56:27,691 --> 00:56:31,018
♪♪

1265
00:56:31,042 --> 00:56:34,768
♪♪

1266
00:56:34,807 --> 00:56:38,698
They're so good, breeze is
beating brake horsepower.

1267
00:56:38,741 --> 00:56:40,724
I cannot keep up with it.

1268
00:56:44,770 --> 00:56:47,122
When do we drink
our own urine?

1269
00:56:47,616 --> 00:56:49,318
Look at that thing now!

1270
00:56:49,342 --> 00:56:52,997
♪♪

1271
00:56:53,021 --> 00:56:57,419
♪♪

1272
00:56:57,492 --> 00:56:58,981
Bloody Nora!

1273
00:56:59,005 --> 00:57:02,341
♪♪

1274
00:57:02,434 --> 00:57:05,466
♪♪

1275
00:57:05,677 --> 00:57:08,677
That is just... fabulous!

1276
00:57:08,701 --> 00:57:12,294
♪♪

1277
00:57:13,817 --> 00:57:16,186
♪♪

1278
00:57:16,270 --> 00:57:19,423
I could have buzzed around
this amazing machine all day,

1279
00:57:19,448 --> 00:57:22,800
but there was still important
environmental work to do.

1280
00:57:22,894 --> 00:57:25,082
So, reluctantly, I broke off

1281
00:57:25,154 --> 00:57:28,043
to rejoin
my stranded colleagues.

1282
00:57:28,965 --> 00:57:32,136
♪♪

1283
00:57:32,261 --> 00:57:34,011
- Are you all right?
- Well, no!

1284
00:57:34,063 --> 00:57:36,761
We've just been left
to drift in a Land Rover!

1285
00:57:36,902 --> 00:57:39,222
Fortunately for you, none of
these ceramic tiles is loose,

1286
00:57:39,268 --> 00:57:41,254
otherwise I'd chuck it
at your head.

1287
00:57:41,278 --> 00:57:44,894
♪♪

1288
00:57:44,918 --> 00:57:48,879
♪♪

1289
00:57:49,011 --> 00:57:50,851
Do you know, I think
it actually handles better

1290
00:57:50,913 --> 00:57:52,543
than it does on land.

1291
00:57:52,722 --> 00:57:55,416
Soon, we will reach
the reef site,

1292
00:57:55,597 --> 00:57:57,419
puncture the inner tubes,
the Land Rover will sink,

1293
00:57:57,443 --> 00:58:00,300
and it will become
a safe haven for cod

1294
00:58:00,349 --> 00:58:04,558
and... haddock and... bream.

1295
00:58:04,582 --> 00:58:06,863
♪♪

1296
00:58:06,921 --> 00:58:08,721
Eventually, we reached the site

1297
00:58:08,754 --> 00:58:11,801
and said about scuttling
our reef machine.

1298
00:58:11,825 --> 00:58:15,872
♪♪

1299
00:58:16,013 --> 00:58:19,536
♪♪

1300
00:58:19,645 --> 00:58:21,614
Fire!

1301
00:58:21,786 --> 00:58:24,346
- Yes!
- Yes!

1302
00:58:28,458 --> 00:58:30,309
Here we go!

1303
00:58:30,474 --> 00:58:32,509
Down! Sink!

1304
00:58:32,643 --> 00:58:34,098
Whoo!

1305
00:58:34,122 --> 00:58:38,242
♪♪

1306
00:58:38,266 --> 00:58:41,390
♪♪

1307
00:58:42,161 --> 00:58:45,078
In truth, all great
environmental projects

1308
00:58:45,164 --> 00:58:47,172
are beset with problems.

1309
00:58:47,269 --> 00:58:50,375
And ours, through no fault
of our own, except James's,

1310
00:58:50,476 --> 00:58:51,945
was no exception.

1311
00:58:54,823 --> 00:58:57,570
Save it! Stop!

1312
00:59:03,853 --> 00:59:05,547
So, in the end, our new reef

1313
00:59:05,640 --> 00:59:08,539
wasn't quite as spectacular
as we'd hoped.

1314
00:59:08,695 --> 00:59:10,117
But it was a start,

1315
00:59:10,202 --> 00:59:12,734
and one day it'll be
the core of something

1316
00:59:12,797 --> 00:59:14,437
a thousand miles long...

1317
00:59:14,597 --> 00:59:16,726
a new and beautiful home

1318
00:59:16,875 --> 00:59:20,726
for the cod and the haddock
of the Caribbean.

1319
00:59:45,377 --> 00:59:46,744
Thank you so much.

1320
00:59:46,815 --> 00:59:49,385
And a very big thank you
to the government of Barbados

1321
00:59:49,440 --> 00:59:50,721
for helping us with that film.

1322
00:59:50,784 --> 00:59:53,807
And we'd just like to say
no coral was damaged

1323
00:59:53,893 --> 00:59:55,346
while we were building our reef.

1324
00:59:55,456 --> 00:59:59,190
No. Or, if we're
perfectly honest, created.

1325
00:59:59,385 --> 01:00:01,342
However, we came back
with a brilliant idea.

1326
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:03,111
You see, we liked it
in the Caribbean.

1327
01:00:03,145 --> 01:00:05,151
You know, our crews liked it
in the Caribbean.

1328
01:00:05,291 --> 01:00:07,393
So we thought it would be
a good idea, next week,

1329
01:00:07,456 --> 01:00:08,385
to make a film

1330
01:00:08,417 --> 01:00:11,119
comparing the motoring
cultures of the French,

1331
01:00:11,120 --> 01:00:12,534
the Dutch
and the British Islands.

1332
01:00:12,621 --> 01:00:14,627
- Yeah, it was a great idea.
- Brilliant idea.

1333
01:00:14,664 --> 01:00:16,002
But Mr Wilman, our producer,

1334
01:00:16,058 --> 01:00:17,932
he decided it wasn't
a brilliant idea,

1335
01:00:17,957 --> 01:00:18,909
and that, instead,

1336
01:00:18,979 --> 01:00:21,354
we should go to northern
France with three old cars

1337
01:00:21,430 --> 01:00:23,414
and drive around in the rain.

1338
01:00:23,854 --> 01:00:25,299
So that's what
we're actually doing.

1339
01:00:25,346 --> 01:00:27,510
And on that terrible
disappointment, it's time to end.

1340
01:00:27,581 --> 01:00:29,135
Thank you so much for watching.

1341
01:00:29,213 --> 01:00:31,807
Thank you for coming.
See you soon. Take care.

1342
01:00:31,881 --> 01:00:33,412
See you next time.

